WEBVTT

00:00:06.919 --> 00:00:15.519
My night has grown long, and the nights'
burden is beyond what I can bear.

00:00:15.520 --> 00:00:28.400
I have been worn down, yet
with You, my Lord, I feel no despair.

00:00:28.401 --> 00:00:37.000
My flaws have burdened my soul,
and my sins have shackled my heart.

00:00:37.001 --> 00:00:43.320
Return, oh soul, and repent
from losing my way, from my wandering.

00:00:43.321 --> 00:00:54.079
How often You call, "O My servants,"
yet I, in my stubbornness...

00:00:54.080 --> 00:01:02.640
wander lost in every valley,
drifting to my right and to my left.

00:01:02.641 --> 00:01:09.280
My wait in this world has been so long;
my sin was of my own choosing.

00:01:09.281 --> 00:01:19.720
Will my apologies save me,
or will my own deeds bring my ruin?

00:01:19.721 --> 00:01:28.439
My night has grown long, and the nights'
burden is beyond what I can bear.

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:36.960
It has taken its toll on me, yet
with You, my Lord, I feel no despair.

00:01:36.961 --> 00:01:47.600
My flaws have burdened my soul,
my sins have shackled my heart.
Return, oh soul, repent from my loss...

00:01:47.601 --> 00:01:54.040
...from my wandering.
My negligence, my ignorance, my falling.

00:01:54.041 --> 00:02:02.600
Will the tears of my return wash it away?
The time has come, my Lord, for me to return.

00:02:02.601 --> 00:02:15.480
I am filled with regret, so accept my reaching out.
I am returning, O Light of my path, driven by my fear and love.

00:02:15.481 --> 00:02:26.560
Trusting in God, my Lord;
in them is my purest devotion.

00:02:26.561 --> 00:02:36.959
My night has grown long, and the nights'
burden is beyond what I can bear.

00:02:36.960 --> 00:02:45.519
I have been worn down, yet
with You, my Lord, I feel no despair.

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:59.480
My flaws have burdened my soul,
my sins have shackled my heart.
Return, oh soul, repent from my loss...

00:02:59.481 --> 00:03:08.640
...from my wandering.

00:03:08.641 --> 00:03:17.319
My night has grown long, and the nights'
burden is beyond what I can bear.

00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:25.480
I have been worn down, yet
with You, my Lord, I feel no despair.

00:03:25.481 --> 00:03:34.159
And my night has grown long, and the nights'
burden is beyond what I can bear.

00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:40.640
I have been worn down, yet
with You, my Lord, I feel no despair.
